sections.content:
Creating new documentation JSONs is a simple process. Here's how you can do it:<br><br><ol><li>Create a new JSON file inside the 'documentation' folder.</li><li>Name the file according to the topic, replacing spaces with underscores (e.g., 'new_topic.json').</li><li>Structure the JSON file with a 'title' and 'sections'. Each section should contain a 'title' and 'content'.</li><li>Save the file, and it will be accessible from the Table of Contents within the application.</li></ol><br>For example:<br><pre>{
    "title": "New Topic",
    "sections": [
        {
            "title": "Subsection",
            "content": "Content goes here..."
        }
    ]
}</pre>
